tafsir[6]{c,v,t}:
  19,96,"Surely those who believe and do deeds of righteousness -- unto them the All-merciful shall assign love."
  20,1,"Ta Ha"
  20,4,"a revelation from Him who created the earth and the high heavens;"
  20,5,"the All-compassionate sat Himself upon the Throne; to Him belongs"
  20,8,"God -- there is no god but He. To Him belong the Names Most Beautiful."
  20,9,"Hast thou received the story of Moses?"